"a.笨重的 【英】 adj. 笨重的 (hard to handle or deal with; unwieldly; clumsy; heavy) 【考】 反义词：easy to handle(易于处理的) 【记】 cumb(睡)+er→睡在( 路上)的→妨碍 【同】 同根词：recumbent( 斜躺的) 【例】 a cumbersome parcel adj. (因沉重或体积大而)难处理的; 笨重的 = clumsy = onerous 【记】源于: cumber(v 阻碍)cumb = cub睡, er－睡在路上的人－妨碍行车. 【参】recumbent(adj 靠着的; 斜躺着的) 【反】easy to handle(易于处理的) 【记】音：扛木板儿 扛着木板时很笨重 cumbersome (adj.)  late 14c., from cumber (v.) + -some (1). Meaning ""unwieldy, hard to carry"" is from 1590s. Related: Cumbersomely; cumbersomeness."
